    management: ["ACE inhibitor or ARB as first-line antiproteinuric therapy — reduce intraglomerular pressure and proteinuria by 30-50%","Corticosteroids for steroid-responsive etiologies (minimal change disease, some FSGS, lupus nephritis)","Immunosuppressive agents for steroid-resistant or steroid-dependent disease: cyclophosphamide, mycophenolate mofetil, calcineurin inhibitors (tacrolimus, cyclosporine), or rituximab","Statin therapy for nephrotic hyperlipidemia (atorvastatin or rosuvastatin)","Dietary sodium restriction (<2 g/day) and moderate protein intake (0.8-1.0 g/kg/day)","Loop diuretics (furosemide) combined with thiazides for refractory edema — monitor for intravascular volume depletion","Anticoagulation for documented thromboembolic events or prophylaxis when serum albumin <2.0-2.5 g/dL","Pneumococcal and influenza vaccination (loss of immunoglobulins increases infection risk)","Treat underlying etiology: glycemic control for diabetic nephropathy, antiviral therapy for hepatitis-related, chemotherapy for malignancy-associated"],
