      type: "Glutamate antagonist / neuroprotective agent",
      action: "Inhibits presynaptic glutamate release, blocks postsynaptic NMDA receptors, and inactivates voltage-gated sodium channels — reduces glutamate-mediated excitotoxicity in ALS motor neurons",
      sideEffects: "Hepatotoxicity (monitor LFTs monthly for first 3 months), nausea, asthenia, dizziness",
