      right: ["Rapid growth, hardening, or new persistent pain in a neurofibroma (suspect MPNST — 8-13% lifetime risk)","Sudden vision loss or visual field deficit from progressive optic pathway glioma","New neurological deficit from spinal cord compression by paraspinal neurofibroma","Severe hypertension with headache, diaphoresis, tachycardia (pheochromocytoma)","Sudden unilateral or bilateral hearing loss (NF2 vestibular schwannoma growth)","Pathological fracture from tibial pseudarthrosis","Signs of brainstem compression from large vestibular schwannoma (NF2): ataxia, facial weakness, dysphagia"]
