    pearls: ["LOC is the MOST SENSITIVE indicator of neurological change — a subtle decline in consciousness often precedes changes in vital signs, pupils, or motor function by hours","GCS ≤8 = intubate: patients with GCS 8 or below cannot protect their airway and require endotracheal intubation to prevent aspiration","ALWAYS check blood glucose FIRST in any patient with altered LOC — hypoglycemia is the most common and most easily reversible cause; treat with dextrose 50% IV immediately if glucose <60 mg/dL","A new unilateral fixed dilated pupil (blown pupil) is a neurosurgical emergency indicating uncal herniation until proven otherwise — notify neurosurgery and administer osmotic therapy immediately","Cushing triad (hypertension, bradycardia, irregular respirations) is a LATE and ominous sign of brainstem herniation — intervention must occur BEFORE this triad develops","Decorticate posturing (flexion) indicates damage ABOVE the brainstem and carries a better prognosis than decerebrate posturing (extension) which indicates brainstem-level damage","Serial GCS documentation with TRENDING is more valuable than a single score — a decline of 2+ points from baseline requires immediate reassessment and provider notification"],
