    pearls: ["TIME IS BRAIN: approximately 1.9 million neurons die per MINUTE during untreated large vessel occlusion — every minute of delay reduces the probability of a good functional outcome","The ischemic cascade: energy failure → glutamate excitotoxicity → calcium influx → free radical production → mitochondrial dysfunction → apoptosis — the PENUMBRA is the target of acute intervention (viable but at risk)","Non-contrast CT is the FIRST imaging study — it rules out hemorrhage (contraindication to tPA) but may NOT show ischemia for 6-12 hours; a NEGATIVE CT in a patient with stroke symptoms SUPPORTS tPA administration","CT perfusion distinguishes ischemic core (irreversible) from penumbra (salvageable) — this mismatch concept extends the thrombectomy window to 24 hours (DAWN/DEFUSE-3 trials)","Permissive hypertension is PROTECTIVE in acute ischemic stroke without tPA — the ischemic penumbra has impaired autoregulation and depends on higher systemic pressure for perfusion; aggressive lowering worsens outcomes","Hypoglycemia (glucose <60 mg/dL) is a critical stroke mimic — ALWAYS check glucose before tPA; other mimics include seizure (Todd paralysis), complex migraine, and conversion disorder","Excitotoxicity is the central mechanism of ischemic neuronal death: ischemia → ATP depletion → failure of Na+/K+-ATPase → depolarization → massive glutamate release → NMDA/AMPA receptor activation → calcium influx → cell death cascade"],
